    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Drain and rinse the\u00a0<strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the\u00a0<strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Slice the\u00a0<strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>\u00a0into 4\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[8]\u00a0</span>wedges</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate the\u00a0<strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-kofte-pitta-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-raita/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the\u00a0<strong>drained chickpeas</strong>\u00a0to a\u00a0<strong>food processor</strong>\u00a0along with the <strong>curry powder</strong>,\u00a0<strong>chopped ginger</strong>,\u00a0<strong>coriander</strong>\u00a0(including the stems), a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Blitz until almost smooth then add the\u00a0<strong>grated\u00a0carrot</strong>\u00a0and pulse for 3 secs further until all of the carrot is incorporated</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-kofte-pitta-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-raita/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the mixture into 4\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span>\u00a0and shape into patties \u2013 these are your\u00a0<strong>chickpea kofte\u00a0patties</strong></p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>baking paper</strong>, drizzle with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>\u00a0and add\u00a0the\u00a0<strong>chickpea kofte\u00a0patties</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over <strong>half</strong> of the\u00a0<strong>nigella seeds</strong>\u00a0(save the rest for later!) and press them gently into the\u00a0patties</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-kofte-pitta-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-raita/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the\u00a0<strong>sweet potatoes</strong>\u00a0(skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the<strong>\u00a0sweet potato</strong> <strong>fries</strong>\u00a0to a large baking tray with a drizzle of\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0and a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt\u00a0</strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the fries are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-kofte-pitta-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-raita/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fries are cooking, finely dice <strong>half</strong> the\u00a0<strong>cucumber</strong>\u00a0then grate the <strong>remaining cucumber</strong></p><p>Squeeze the water out of the\u00a0<strong>grated cucumber</strong>\u00a0then add to a bowl along with the <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>and <strong>mint sauce</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>raita</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-kofte-pitta-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-raita/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash the<strong> baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>diced cucumber</strong> to a bowl along with the <strong>baby leaf\u00a0salad</strong>,\u00a0juice of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> <strong>lemon wedge</strong> and the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>nigella seeds </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>cucumber salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-kofte-pitta-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-raita/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the kofte\u00a0patties\u00a0are almost done, add the <strong>wholemeal pittas</strong> to the tray with the sweet potato fries\u00a0and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p><p>Carefully slice in half before serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-kofte-pitta-with-sweet-potato-fries-and-raita/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dollop your <strong>raita</strong>\u00a0into the pitta pockets then fill with the\u00a0<strong>chickpea</strong> <strong>kofte patties</strong>\u00a0and a spoonful of <strong>mango chutney</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>sweet potato fries</strong>,\u00a0<strong>cucumber salad </strong>and<strong> remaining lemon wedges</strong>\u00a0to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
